  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "QA/QC Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Must possess <strong>welding inspector certification of American Welding Society (AWS)</strong>  or <strong>CSWIP 3.1 (Welding Inspector)</strong> certification.</li><li>Implement and maintain <strong>QA/QC procedures</strong> for construction works, particularly <strong>chemical and industrial piping installation</strong>.</li><li>Conduct inspections to ensure works comply with <strong>project specifications, drawings, codes, and quality standards</strong>.</li><li>Prepare and manage <strong>Inspection & Test Plans (ITP)</strong>, method statements, and quality records.</li><li>Coordinate with project teams, clients, consultants, and third-party inspectors on quality matters.</li><li>Monitor site workmanship and ensure corrective actions are taken for non-conformances.</li><li>Prepare <strong>QA/QC reports</strong>, inspection records, and handover documentation.</li><li>Support testing, flushing, pressure testing, and commissioning activities.</li><li>Promote quality awareness and compliance on site.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in <strong>Mechanical Engineering, Quality Engineering, or related discipline</strong>.</li><li>Preferably <strong>2–5 years of relevant QA/QC experience</strong> in construction projects.</li><li>Experience in <strong>piping systems, industrial or semiconductor projects</strong> is an advantage.</li><li>Knowledge of QA/QC documentation, inspection procedures, and construction standards.</li><li>Able to interpret <strong>engineering drawings and specifications</strong>.</li><li>Detail-oriented  with good organizational skills.</li><li>Willing to work on construction sites.</li></ul>",
